-------JDK & IDE--------------
    To start coding with Java, you'll need two things:
    1. A Java Development Kit (JDK): It contains a compiler, a compiler will compile your source code, your written code into byte code, which can run on a machine. To Download JDK, search for "jdk download" (can be from the oracle website).
    2. A Integrated Development Enviroment (IDE): An IDE is a fancy term for a workspace in which we can write code, because sometimes notepad can just not be good enough. To Donwload IDE, search for "intelliJ download".

    IMPORTANT: to run your code, on terminal:
    1. javac YourFileName.java (This compiles the file into YourFileName.class)
    2. java YourFileName (This runs the compiled code; do not include the file extension here).

